Class BallotFileChooser

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
public class BallotFileChooser
extends javax.swing.JFileChooser
A file chooser interface which allows a user to navigate the file system and select either ballot files or a directory. This is provided through the invocation of methods to selected either ballot files or a single directory, respectively.

  • Constructor Details

    • BallotFileChooser

      public BallotFileChooser​(java.awt.Component parent)
      Creates the file chooser and sets its parent to the given component. The ability for the user to select just any file is disabled in the constructor as well, so that users must abide by the options presented by the file chooser. Other options are set dynamically (not in the constructor) for invocations to select files or directories.
      Parameters:
      parent - the component that will own this file chooser.

  • Method Details

    • ChooseBallotFiles

      public java.io.File[] ChooseBallotFiles()
      Allows the user to select multiple ballot files through a file chooser. The user can see directories and files with valid extensions while navigating. Users are only allowed to select files whose extensions are those of valid ballot files. The files selected by the user are filtered so that only the files that pass this filter are returned. Null is returned if the user aborts the selection process. An empty array is returned if no valid ballot files are found in the user's selection.
      Returns:
      an array of files selected by the user, if any.
      See Also:
      ChooseDirectory(), FilterForBallotFiles(File[] selected_files)

    • ChooseDirectory

      public java.io.File[] ChooseDirectory()
      Allows the user to select a single directory through a file chooser. The user can only see directories while navigating (not files). The files in the directory (but not in any subdirectories) selected by the user are filtered so that only the files whose extensions are those of valid ballot files are returned. Null is returned if the user aborts the selection process. An empty array is returned if no valid ballot files are found in the selected directory.
      Returns:
      an array of files from the directory selected by the user, if any.
      See Also:
      ChooseBallotFiles(), FilterForBallotFiles(File[] selected_files)
